U.K.’s Starmer set to meet with Trump in Oval Office today President Donald Trump is scheduled to meet Thursday with British Prime Minister Keir Starmer in the Oval Office as the U.K. leader seeks to make a case for Trump to support Ukraine amid its war with Russia. Starmer is the second European leader to visit Trump this week to make a case for continued U.S. support of Ukraine; French President Emmanuel Macron met with Trump on Monday. Macron and Starmer have argued that U.S. security guarantees are vital for any potential Ukraine-Russia peace deal to last. Trump did not make those guarantees in his meeting with Macron. Speaking to reporters Wednesday during the first Cabinet meeting of his second term, Trump dismissed the idea he would make strong U.S. security guarantees for Ukraine. Trump has falsely claimed that Ukraine started the war with Russia and called Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelensky a dictator, while declining to label Russian President Vladimir Putin as one. Zelensky is scheduled to meet Trump on Friday at the White House.
